            {
              "id": "SNYK-JAVA-COMH2DATABASE-3009896",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Low severity - Insecure Permissions vulnerability in com.h2database:h2"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2018-14335) com.h2database:h2@1.4.193"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "* Package Manager: maven\n* Vulnerable module: com.h2database:h2\n* Introduced through: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917 and com.h2database:h2@1.4.193\n### Detailed paths\n* _Introduced through_: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917 › com.h2database:h2@1.4.193\n# Overview\n[com.h2database:h2](http://www.h2database.com/html/main.html) is a database engine\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to Insecure Permissions in the backup function which allows attackers to read sensitive files (out of their permissions scope) via a symlink to a fake database file.\r\n\r\n**Note:** \r\nThis is exploitable only if users misconfigured applications with excessive permissions.\r\nThe documentation of H2 contains all necessary warnings for insecure configuration options and suggests security constraints for H2 Console servlet.\r\n\r\nAccording to the above, this is a low severity vulnerability because of the low likelihood of it being exploited.\n# Remediation\nUpgrade `com.h2database:h2` to version 1.4.198 or higher.\n# References\n- [Exploit DB](https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/45105)\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/h2database/h2database/commit/64a778cc2e306da3d3f4cb10e12caee83f74ee40)\n- [GitHub Issue](https://github.com/h2database/h2database/issues/1294)\n"
              },
              "properties": {
