            {
              "id": "SNYK-JAVA-ORGAPACHETOMCATEMBED-1048292",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Medium severity - Information Exposure vulnerability in org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2020-17527) org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core@8.5.6"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "* Package Manager: maven\n* Vulnerable module: org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core\n* Introduced through: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917, org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-web@1.4.3.RELEASE and others\n### Detailed paths\n* _Introduced through_: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917 › org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-web@1.4.3.RELEASE › org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-tomcat@1.4.3.RELEASE › org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core@8.5.6\n# Overview\n[org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core](https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core) is a Core Tomcat implementation.\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to Information Exposure. An HTTP request header value could be reused from the previous stream received on an HTTP/2 connection for the request associated with the subsequent stream. While this would most likely lead to an error and the closure of the HTTP/2 connection, it is possible that information could leak between requests.\n# Remediation\nUpgrade `org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core` to version 8.5.60, 9.0.40, 10.0.0-M10 or higher.\n# References\n- [Apache Tomcat Bug Report](https://bz.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=64830)\n- [forese01 PoC](https://github.com/forse01/CVE-2020-17527-Tomcat)\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/apache/tomcat/commit/d56293f816d6dc9e2b47107f208fa9e95db58c65)\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-200",
                  "maven"
                ],
