            {
              "id": "SNYK-JAVA-ORGAPACHETOMCATEMBED-15989812",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Medium severity - Improper Encoding or Escaping of Output vulnerability in org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2026-34483) org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core@8.5.6"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "* Package Manager: maven\n* Vulnerable module: org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core\n* Introduced through: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917, org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-web@1.4.3.RELEASE and others\n### Detailed paths\n* _Introduced through_: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917 › org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-web@1.4.3.RELEASE › org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-tomcat@1.4.3.RELEASE › org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core@8.5.6\n# Overview\n[org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core](https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core) is a Core Tomcat implementation.\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to Improper Encoding or Escaping of Output in `JsonAccessLogValve()`, which relies on an unescaped `append()` in generating JSON logs. If non-default values are used for the Connector attributes `relaxedPathChars` or `relaxedQueryChars`, an attacker can inject malicious JSON into logs.\n# Remediation\nUpgrade `org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core` to version 9.0.117, 10.1.54, 11.0.21 or higher.\n# References\n- [Apache Mailing List](https://lists.apache.org/thread/j1w7304yonlr8vo1tkb5nfs7od1y228b)\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/apache/tomcat/commit/f9ddc24fcfcdfaea4a6953198d8636aca3e957bc)\n- [OSS Security Advisory](http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2026/04/09/26)\n"
              },
