            {
              "id": "SNYK-JAVA-ORGHIBERNATE-584563",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "High severity - SQL Injection vulnerability in org.hibernate:hibernate-core"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2019-14900) org.hibernate:hibernate-core@5.0.11.Final"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "* Package Manager: maven\n* Vulnerable module: org.hibernate:hibernate-core\n* Introduced through: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917, org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-data-jpa@1.4.3.RELEASE and others\n### Detailed paths\n* _Introduced through_: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917 › org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-data-jpa@1.4.3.RELEASE › org.hibernate:hibernate-core@5.0.11.Final\n# Overview\n[org.hibernate:hibernate-core](https://github.com/hibernate/hibernate-orm) is a library providing Object/Relational Mapping (ORM) support to applications, libraries, and frameworks.\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to SQL Injection. A SQL injection in the implementation of the JPA Criteria API can permit unsanitized literals when a literal is used in the SELECT or GROUP BY parts of the query. This flaw could allow an attacker to access unauthorized information or possibly conduct further attacks.\n# Remediation\nUpgrade `org.hibernate:hibernate-core` to version 5.3.18.Final, 5.4.18.Final or higher.\n# References\n- [GitHub Pull Request](https://github.com/hibernate/hibernate-orm/pull/3438)\n- [Jira Ticket](https://hibernate.atlassian.net/browse/HHH-14077)\n"
              },
