            {
              "id": "SNYK-JAVA-ORGSPRINGFRAMEWORKSECURITY-8399269",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Medium severity - Authorization Bypass vulnerability in org.springframework.security:spring-security-core"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2024-38827) org.springframework.security:spring-security-core@4.1.4.RELEASE"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "* Package Manager: maven\n* Vulnerable module: org.springframework.security:spring-security-core\n* Introduced through: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917, org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-security@1.2.0.RELEASE and others\n### Detailed paths\n* _Introduced through_: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917 › org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-security@1.2.0.RELEASE › org.springframework.security:spring-security-config@4.1.4.RELEASE › org.springframework.security:spring-security-core@4.1.4.RELEASE\n# Overview\n[org.springframework.security:spring-security-core](http://spring.io/spring-security) is a package that provides security services for the Spring IO Platform.\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to Authorization Bypass due to the use of `String.toLowerCase()` and `String.toUpperCase()` that have `Locale` dependent exceptions, which results in authorization rules not working properly.\n# Remediation\nUpgrade `org.springframework.security:spring-security-core` to version 5.7.14, 5.8.16, 6.2.8, 6.3.5 or higher.\n# References\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/commit/0eaffb37e7f10f30fdbba1d3728e66e26837ff89)\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/commit/a7bf8f7cc68d95ce30f18722f5d441ea3fa798f4)\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/commit/a8c4d6ceada54d150ab21b6489b5c9d1c657b889)\n- [Spring Security Advisory](https://spring.io/security/cve-2024-38827)\n"
              },
