            {
              "id": "SNYK-JAVA-ORGSPRINGFRAMEWORKSECURITY-2833359",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "High severity - Authorization Bypass vulnerability in org.springframework.security:spring-security-web"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2022-22978) org.springframework.security:spring-security-web@4.1.4.RELEASE"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "* Package Manager: maven\n* Vulnerable module: org.springframework.security:spring-security-web\n* Introduced through: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917, org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-security@1.2.0.RELEASE and others\n### Detailed paths\n* _Introduced through_: com.myapp:wezvatech-demo@9739110917 › org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-security@1.2.0.RELEASE › org.springframework.security:spring-security-web@4.1.4.RELEASE\n# Overview\n[org.springframework.security:spring-security-web](https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.springframework.security/spring-security-web) is a package within Spring Security that provides security services for the Spring IO Platform.\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to Authorization Bypass via the `RegexRequestMatcher` class,  which can easily be misconfigured to be bypassed on some servlet containers when it is used with `.` in the regular expression.\n# Remediation\nUpgrade `org.springframework.security:spring-security-web` to version 5.4.11, 5.5.7, 5.6.4 or higher.\n# References\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/commit/0dcb592b03c229874f5a560c26c39b5941a88b33)\n- [GitHub Fix Commit v5.5.7](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/commit/c6461d61babfcf92febfd0a85785623e53190a8f)\n- [GitHub Fix Commit v5.6.4](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/commit/70863952aeb9733499027714d38821db05654856)\n- [GitHub Issue](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/11234)\n- [PoC](https://github.com/ducluongtran9121/CVE-2022-22978-PoC)\n- [VMware Tanzu Security Advisory](https://tanzu.vmware.com/security/cve-2022-22978)\n"
              },
